gomodel:SYNGO_2394  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: GPC4-Fc reduces LRRTM4 induced presynaptic differentiation in coculture assays.\nGPC4 knockdown decreases synapse formation onto LRRTM4-expressing HEK cells in coculture assays.. Experimental description: Experimental Procedures\nNeuronal Cultures\nHippocampal neurons were cultured from P0 Long-Evans rats (Charles River).\n\n6/2/2028 Pim\n- Overexpressed GPC4 is of mouse species: \"Full-length cDNAs encoding mouse LRRTM4 (accession number AY182031), human LRRTM4 (BC110058), and mouse glypicans GPC1 (BC062902), GPC2 (BC083180), GPC3 (BC036126), GPC4 (BC006622), GPC5 (BC115712) and GPC6 (BC023448) were purchased from Open Biosystems/Thermo Scientific. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2394" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

